  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "Currently, valued params (AKA non flags), support only one value. For example:\r\n```\r\nnpx buidler mytask --threshold 100\r\n```\r\n\r\nIs there any interest from the community on allowing multiple values per-param? Such as:\r\n```\r\n# 'gas-range' would be a 2-value param, imagine [min, max]  \r\nnpx buidler mytask --gas-range 100 500\r\n```\r\nOr alternatively:\r\n```\r\n# here the [min, max] param values would be parsed in the same order as they appear\r\nnpx buidler mytask --gas-range 100 --gas-range 500\r\n```\r\nA first implementation would allow N-arity params where N is known beforehand, otherwise having _variadic_ param values could lead to ambiguous situations combined with other params.",
