    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Personal opinion:\r\n\r\n`--gas-range 100 500` is something you _can_ have, but I think it's not common to use this kind of interface in the command line.\r\n\r\n`--gas-range 100 --gas-range 500` is a little better, but the problem for this example is that using a flag multiple times is usually interpreted as a list of values that should probably not be order-dependent. I think of this as similar to sending multiple values in a query string, where `foo=1&foo=2` is usually interpreted as `foo = [1, 2]` in application code. A common example is something like `--ignore-dir`, where you might want to specify it multiple times.\r\n\r\nI mean, for the particular case of `--gas-range`, I would suggest using `--gas-range 100,500`, but supporting multiple flags as a way of specifying a list of values seems like a good idea.",
